name: Important notes!
info:
Setup globals for the various flows, it is triggered on each deploy. You may want to disable this when developing new tests. This is done by unchecking the ddd option in the Inject node.

## Global variables
 - The **workspace** folder contains sample data and configurations. 
 - The **email** address is used to send all email communication to the specified email address.
 - 

## Connect resources
The workspace folder contains a manifest.json file. The resources section references Connect resources in the workspace folder. These resources are automatically uploaded to the OL Connect Server (file store) on each deployment. The resources are marked as permanent so they are not deleted by the Connect's cleanup service.

name: Dynamic template
info:
Add the _template_ query parameter to set the template.

When the parameter is omitted it will use the fallback template.

When the template is not found on the server the Catch node is triggered.

name: Data is stored to disk (XML) for the fun of it.
info: Depending on the workflow of the customer that data will be stored on disk, in a database or passed to proprietary end point. For sake of simplicity we are saving the data to disk... change to your requirements.

name: Note! We could use the JSON data here but lets try dataRecordId
info: Being lazy here... let the datamapper handle the nested data for the details rather than us having to write that data in a function node.

name: Respond early & delete
info:
We are responding early here so the app does not need to wait till the PDF has created.

name: Why use the watchdirectory node?
info: The native node watcher is low level, it triggers the "add file" event before file is completed written. It then would require a Trigger (delay) and RBE node to properly process the file.
